But I do not agree because you have to at least ask something in order to know they it is intelligble responses.  I have been following the Audio ITC of Debbie Caruso (www.listentothisforme.com/) and it seems like this is legitimate responses.

At times here all I hear is intelligible garbbled radio speak that people are interpreting as conversation.  As the radio scans you can easily confuse this garbled radio as messages from the beyond; however, if you get intelligent responses from some questions or conversation then you can reasonably state that it is a conversation from the beyond - as long as the conversation is enough to be able to make that claim.

To claim a binch of munged words from a series of radio stations is conversation without any real connection / q&a is really stretching it I think.  Again, I am not a skeptic, but I think fashioning conversation out of garbled words from radio stations is rediculous.


DBMDude

